This paper deals with photorealistic style transfer, which involves generating images that preserve the structure and detail of the content image while transferring the style of another image. This task is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR), as it involves image processing and manipulation. The paper also mentions the use of a high-resolution network, which suggests that it may be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as high-resolution image generation is a challenging task that requires advanced machine learning techniques. Finally, the paper presents experimental results and compares its approach to existing methods, which indicates that it may be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) as well.
